# Dashboard Typography Standard

Apply this standard to Worker layout pages and mirror the same structure in Admin/Employer dashboard shells.

- Base body/content text uses `DM Sans` (default body font, no custom override).
- Section/page titles use `Syne` via `h1/h2/h3` or explicit `.font-display`.
- Numeric highlight metrics (KPI/value blocks) use `Syne` with `font-semibold`.
- Descriptive helper text, metadata lines, and button labels stay on `DM Sans`.
- Do not introduce third font families in dashboard surfaces.
- Keep typography consistent across `WorkerLayout`, `AdminDashboard`, and `EmployerDashboard`.
- For new dashboard components, reuse `WorkerSectionHeader`/dashboard primitives typography rhythm instead of ad-hoc font decisions.

## Quick Mapping

- **Title / Heading** -> `Syne` (`h1/h2/h3` or `.font-display`)
- **Body / Supporting Text** -> `DM Sans`
- **Action Labels (buttons/nav)** -> `DM Sans`
- **KPI / Emphasis Values** -> `Syne`
